#   ARRAY
Collection of similar type of data
Syntax:  datatype var[size];

Whenever we need to store a data elements of a type
Array index start from zero because zero refers directly to first address. In case 12
Array is a best example of static allocation

# Array 2D:
Syntax: datatype var[rows][cols];

By default access is row and cols(row wise access)

# Strings

Collection of characters from C++ character setting.
'a' character
"aryan" string

String can store any info that falls within the character set of C++

cin>>var; -> Can only read a word   //tokenizes on basis of space

getline(cin,var);  

By default, the system insert a null symbol'\0' to denote the end od a string
string n="aryan"